rComments: Like really you can't find a better prof at utsc. He's the best. Teaches very well, explains concepts clearly, fair exams. Very gentle and patient. One midterm, one final, one written assignment (10%). All notes are hand-written in class on boards so you have to attend classes.

One of the best prof!!!!! Love his lectures, so passionate and inspirational. Midterm is fair. But final is really another thing. Much harder than midterm. Good course for those who are good at understanding every details.
Best everrr! Given that you attend the lectures, it's an easy A
teacherRatingTags: ['Lecture heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Amazing lectures']

rComments: Best prof ever.
One of the best profs I've  had at UTSC!

Great Prof. Very approachable! Go to his office hours if you need help/clarification he is a prof who genuinely cares where or not you understand the material. Just go to class, listen to what he says, study your notes and practice problems and you can easily get 90+ on his midterm. The final is a different story, didn't expect it to be so hard.

Very energetic and dynamic prof. 1 midterm & 1 final. The final was very unexpectedly challenging.. considering the midterm was fair/doable (75% class avg). This is prob one of the most interesting courses I've enrolled in. He's an EXTREMELY approachable/friendly prof.. always punctual & willing to help! Would take another class w/ him again.
Awesome Prof. Explained stuff very well but final were kinda hard.

As a teacher he is good.  But my experience is, his midterm and finals are never what you studied for because he likes to challenge you mathematically by changing a little in EVERY question.  For my friends who are good in math, they do okay...  If you're those that learn concept A in class and is able to answer what is "A + B".  Take the course.
The BEST prof ever! He's very helpful n' his lectures are interesting!
One of best professors I have ever had. Explained the material very well, however, don't expect his exams to be easy.
Easy midterm but extremly hard final exam. Dropped 10% from midterm mark. His final exam is much harder than previous years.
